I see people raising three fingers.

00:13:55.040 --> 00:13:56.260
And I see people raising four fingers.

00:13:56.860 --> 00:14:00.220
I don't see anyone answering number one.

00:14:01.260 --> 00:14:03.820
So the general idea seems to be that either they're on opposite

00:14:03.820 --> 00:14:05.540
sides, or maybe one of them is on the plane.

00:14:07.040 --> 00:14:08.940
Well, let's try to see.

00:14:09.420 --> 00:14:10.640
Is one of them on the plane?

00:14:11.800 --> 00:14:13.420
Well, let's check.

00:14:14.300 --> 00:14:16.600
OK, so let's look at the point.

00:14:16.820 --> 00:14:19.360
Sorry, I have one more blackboard to use here.

00:14:25.400 --> 00:14:30.240
So I take the point Q0, which is at minus 1, 2, 2.

00:14:30.880 --> 00:14:34.760
Well, if I plug that into the plane equation,

00:14:35.760 --> 00:14:44.300
so x plus 2y plus 4z will equal minus 1 plus 2 times 2 plus 4

00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:45.000
times 2.

00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:51.620
That's, well, 4 plus 8, 12 minus 11.

00:14:52.520 --> 00:14:54.640
That, I think, is bigger than 7.

00:14:55.560 --> 00:14:58.520
OK, so Q0 is not in the plane.

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:02.480
Let's try again with Q1.

00:15:04.960 --> 00:15:07.100
1, 3, negative 1.

00:15:08.160 --> 00:15:12.500
Well, if we plug that into x plus 2y plus 4z,

00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:17.100
we'll have 1 plus 2 times 3 makes 7.

00:15:17.360 --> 00:15:20.660
But we add 4 times negative 1.

00:15:20.840 --> 00:15:23.140
We end up with 3 less than 7.

00:15:23.620 --> 00:15:25.560
Well, that one is not in the plane either.

00:15:25.560 --> 00:15:30.200
So I don't think, actually, that the answer should be number 3.

00:15:32.420 --> 00:15:34.920
So let's get rid of answer number 3.

00:15:40.100 --> 00:15:42.220
OK, let's see, in the light of this,

