00:15:57.820 --> 00:15:58.800
So let's think about it.

00:15:59.940 --> 00:16:01.340
These points are not in the plane,

00:16:01.540 --> 00:16:03.200
but they're not in the plane in different ways.

00:16:03.480 --> 00:16:05.580
One of them somehow overshudes, we get 11.

00:16:05.820 --> 00:16:07.400
They're one, we only get 3.

00:16:07.640 --> 00:16:08.400
That's less than 7.

00:16:09.420 --> 00:16:12.380
If you think about how a plane splits space

00:16:12.380 --> 00:16:14.840
into two half spaces on either side,

00:16:15.900 --> 00:16:18.980
well, one of them is going to be the points

00:16:18.980 --> 00:16:22.920
where x plus 2y plus 4z is less than 7.

00:16:23.700 --> 00:16:29.800
And the other one will be, so that's somehow this side.

00:16:30.340 --> 00:16:31.480
And that's where q1 is.

00:16:31.940 --> 00:16:39.780
And the other side is where x plus 2y plus 4z

00:16:39.780 --> 00:16:41.180
is actually bigger than 7.

00:16:44.520 --> 00:16:48.180
And to go from one to the other, well,

00:16:49.820 --> 00:16:52.780
x plus 2y plus 4z needs to go through the value 7.

00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:56.940
If you're moving along any path from q0 to q1,

00:16:58.020 --> 00:17:01.660
this thing will change continuously from 11 to 3.

00:17:01.820 --> 00:17:03.380
At some time, it has to go through 7.

00:17:04.520 --> 00:17:05.380
Does that make sense?

00:17:06.560 --> 00:17:09.420
So to go from q0 to q1, we need to cross-peer at some place.

00:17:10.400 --> 00:17:12.300
So there are no opposite sides.

00:17:33.100 --> 00:17:37.260
Now, that doesn't quite finish answering

00:17:37.260 --> 00:17:42.160
the question that we had, which was where does the line intersect

00:17:42.160 --> 00:17:42.660
the plane?

00:17:44.600 --> 00:17:48.040
But while we can do the same thing, now we know not only

00:17:48.040 --> 00:17:52.100
the points q0 and q1, we know actually any point on the line

00:17:52.100 --> 00:17:55.600
because we have a geometric equation of ver telling us

00:17:55.600 --> 00:17:58.540
where is the point that's moving on the line at time t?

00:18:02.060 --> 00:18:05.620
So what about the moving point q of t?

00:18:06.340 --> 00:18:09.620
Well, let's plug its coordinates into the plane equation.

00:18:10.220 --> 00:18:16.360
So we'll take x of t plus twice y of t plus 4z of t.

00:18:17.640 --> 00:18:26.720
That's equal to, well, minus 1 plus 2t plus twice 2 plus t

00:18:26.720 --> 00:18:31.200
plus 4 times 2 minus 3t.

00:18:34.240 --> 00:18:40.040
So if you simplify this a bit, you get 2t plus 2t minus 12t.

00:18:40.460 --> 00:18:42.200
That should be minus 8t.

00:18:43.220 --> 00:18:47.020
And the constant term is minus 1 plus 4 plus 8 is 11.

00:18:49.120 --> 00:18:54.540
And we have to compare that with 7.

00:18:55.340 --> 00:18:57.220
Question is, is this other equal to 7?

00:18:58.720 --> 00:19:12.580
Well, so q of t is in the plane exactly when minus 8t plus 11

00:19:12.580 --> 00:19:14.460
equals 7.

00:19:15.700 --> 00:19:18.420
And that's the same, if you manipulate this,

00:19:18.560 --> 00:19:21.040
you will get t equals 1 half.

00:19:24.960 --> 00:19:27.240
In fact, that's not very surprising.

00:19:27.840 --> 00:19:30.160
If you look at these values 11 and 3,

00:19:30.520 --> 00:19:33.520
you see that 7 is actually right in between.

00:19:33.840 --> 00:19:35.080
It's the average of these two numbers.

00:19:36.020 --> 00:19:40.160
So it would make sense that it's halfway in between q 0 and q 1

00:19:40.160 --> 00:19:41.440
that we will get 7.

00:19:46.720 --> 00:19:50.200
And then at that time, q at time 1 half

00:19:50.200 --> 00:19:52.120
well, let's plug the values.

00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:58.780
So minus 1 plus 2t will be 0.

00:20:00.640 --> 00:20:04.580
2 plus t will be 2 and a half, or 5 halves.

00:20:05.820 --> 00:20:10.000
And 2 minus 3 halves will be 1 half.

00:20:12.860 --> 00:20:16.380
So this is where the line intersects the plane.

00:20:43.080 --> 00:20:47.120
So you see that's actually a pretty easy way of finding where a line

00:20:47.120 --> 00:20:48.400
intersects each other.

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:53.500
If we can find a parametric equation of the line and an equation of the plane,

00:20:54.020 --> 00:20:59.740
then we basically just plug one into the other and see at what time the moving point hits the plane.

00:21:00.480 --> 00:21:01.500
And then we know where it is.

